{"ts":"2026-06-26T17:53:13.627Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Refining UI Elements**\n\nI'm now detailing user interface refinements. I've conceived of a \"Vault/History\" button with a badge for saved blueprint counts. There is a planned privacy notice, presented as an enterprise-grade card to stress that all data is local with no telemetry. I also plan for a \"Local History Drawer,\" a sliding panel showcasing a timeline of saved blueprints with quick load/delete functions.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-26T17:53:15.063Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Defining Reset Logic**\n\nI'm now clarifying the reset behavior. A reset action triggers a full data wipe, returning the user to the starting point. I'm also considering the mobile strategy; I'm planning for floating action buttons to collapse on smaller screens and a full-width sliding drawer. Accessibility is a key focus, ensuring keyboard navigation, tab order, and screen reader compatibility.\n\nI'm also specifying which files to change (`BlueprintGenerator.tsx`) and, importantly, which to leave untouched. Finally, I'm defining the `gff_blueprint_history` structure for local storage, including save timestamp, wizard data, score, category, solution title, impact, and dimensions.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-26T17:53:16.685Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Structuring Output Content**\n\nI'm now detailing the output content structure to ensure a professional look. I've composed a copy text template for the clipboard, designed to mimic a senior architect's output, with sections for organizational profile, assessments, and the target GFF AI topology, aiming for a high-integrity, structured presentation. The goal is to provide summaries, or provide the data used to create summaries, where we don't need to recalculate.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
{"ts":"2026-06-26T17:53:17.754Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Refining Print Styling**\n\nI'm now integrating print styling. I'm focusing on ensuring clean print outputs, so I'm investigating Tailwind's built-in `print:` utilities for hiding non-printable elements. I'm thinking about how to hide navigation, action buttons, headers, and footers when printing. I also plan to force background colors and optimize text for high contrast. This will integrate cleanly into the current build.\n\n\n","redacted":false}}
