dBlueprint`, including a unique ID, timestamp, user data, and the final results. I'm defining the `STORAGE_KEY` and preparing the methods to load history from local storage using `useState`. I'm starting to write the load and save methods.\n\n\n**Implementing Local Storage**\n\nI'm now implementing the local storage functionality for saving and retrieving blueprint history, ensuring it's robust and error-safe. I've integrated `useEffect` to load the history on component mount and implemented a `try...catch` block to gracefully handle potential parsing errors from `localStorage`. I'm working to write the save function next.\n\n\n**Refining Data Persistence**\n\nI've just finished the save function, focusing on preventing duplicate entries based on email and score/industry. I implemented a filter to keep the history list clean, limiting it to the most recent 10 items. I also added a `try...catch` block to handle potential storage errors. I'm now writing the delete functionality for the history drawer.\n\n\n**Finalizing Local History**\n\nI've just written the delete function for the history drawer, ensuring items are removed from both state and local storage. Now, I'm integrating the load/restore function to easily retrieve saved blueprints. Additionally, I've defined a reset function to clear the loaded state. Finally, I'm examining how to format the \"copy to clipboard\" summary text.\n\n\n**Formatting the Summary**\n\nI'm now formatting the \"copy to clipboard\" summary text for optimal readability. I want a clean, structured presentation that includes the generation date, status, organizational profile, assessment scores, and the recommended solution. I'm focusing on clearly labeling each section and presenting the data in an easily digestible format.\n\n\n**Designing Print Action**\n\nOkay, I'm now crafting the print functionality for the blueprint summary. My focus is on ensuring a clean, presentable print output, so I'm investigating how to hide non-essential UI elements like the left-hand navigation, the toolbar, and bottom CTAs when printing. I'm also ensuring the confidentiality note and generated text is printed.\n\n\n**Designing Print Action**\n\nI'm now crafting the print functionality. I'm focusing on a clean enterprise PDF format and identified elements to hide. I'll use print utilities, wrapping the main result display in a print-ready container and applying `print:hidden` to the header, sidebar, live variable buffer, action toolbar buttons, and the bottom CTA. The goal is a clean, printable output.\n\n\n**Analyzing Print Styles**\n\nI'm now investigating the project's styling approach (CSS Modules, standard CSS, styled-jsx) to determine the best method for injecting print-specific styles. I'm considering using a normal `<style>` tag for maximum compatibility. My aim is to create a print-friendly view.\n\n\n**Designing Print Preferences**\n\nI'm now implementing the print-specific CSS. I'm focusing on ensuring black text on a white background for ink savings, overriding the default dark theme. I'm designing a print-friendly layout with a light background and dark text, using `!important` to override. I'm evaluating the color scheme and layout. I'm working on the design of the action buttons now.\n\n\n**Positioning the Action Bar**\n\nI'm now integrating the action toolbar between the \"Blueprint Synthesized\" card and the circular score dial. I've conceptualized it as a dark, premium panel to match the interface. My primary focus is on designing an enterprise-grade toolbar, ensuring an appropriate aesthetic.\n\n\n**Refining Copy and Print**\n\nI'm now implementing the copy-to-clipboard function within the action bar. Then, I'm focusing on refining the print functionality. I'm reviewing the existing print styles and optimizing the print layout. I'm focusing on creating a clean, professional print output.\n\n\n**Implementing Copy Functionality**\n\nI'm now implementing the copy functionality, focusing on handling both success and error states. I've integrated a visual feedback mechanism using an SVG icon to indicate when the summary has been successfully copied. I'm also ensuring a consistent user experience. I'm focusing on ensuring the styling aligns with the design system.\n\n\n**Finalizing Error Handling**\n\nI'm now implementing more robust error handling for the copy function, including displaying user-friendly feedback. I've also refactored the action bar component and its styling for better modularity. I'm focusing on providing clear visual cues for success and failure states.\n\n\n\n**Optimizing Save Functionality**\n\nI'm now optimizing the save functionality, specifically focusing on the local save feature. I want to improve the user experience and ensure smooth data handling. I'm reviewing the save button integration to ensure the save locally functionality is working as expected.\n\n\n\n**Refining UI Enhancements**\n\nI'm now integrating the privacy note card, strategically placing it below the action toolbar within the rendered result. I've focused on ensuring the visual hierarchy and readability of the note. I'm also preparing to test the new design.\n\n\n**Designing the Privacy Note**\n\nI've just finalized the design of the privacy note, ensuring it's clearly visible and easy to understand. I've focused on using clear language and a visually appealing layout to emphasize the tool's zero-data transmission guarantee. I also made sure it complements the overall aesthetic of the application.\n\n\n**Positioning the Vault**\n\nI'm now carefully placing the \"Saved Blueprints Vault\" button within the Top Title Section. I'm focusing on aesthetic placement while maintaining intuitive usability. I'm imagining how this element, which will be a trigger for the Local History Drawer, will blend with the generator's title.\n\n\n**Refining Vault Placement**\n\nI'm now integrating the \"Saved Blueprints Vault\" button into the Top Title Section, adding it to the right-hand side of the header. I'm focusing on ensuring it aesthetically complements the title and offers intuitive usability, serving as the trigger for the Local History Drawer. I have confirmed placement.\n\n\n\n**Designing the Drawer**\n\nI'm now designing the Local History Drawer component, envisioning a sliding panel directly within the `BlueprintGenerator`. My focus is creating an elegant and functional UI using Tailwind CSS to ensure a seamless user experience. I'm focusing on its layout.\n\n\n**Implementing the Drawer**\n\nI'm now implementing the Local History Drawer's core structure and behavior, focusing on its open/close state. The modal includes a backdrop for focus management. I am developing its appearance and responsiveness using Tailwind CSS, and ensuring accessibility and ease of use.\n\n\n**Refining the Drawer Content**\n\nI'm now populating the Local History Drawer with saved blueprint previews, focusing on displaying essential information like dates and titles. I'm dynamically generating these previews from the saved data to improve data handling, and optimizing performance.\n\n\n**Populating the Drawer**\n\nI'm now populating the Local History Drawer with saved blueprints, displaying a short description and ensuring the display reflects current history data. I'm focusing on providing users with a clear and concise view of the stored blueprints. I am now focusing on the presentation logic.\n\n\n**Populating the Drawer**\n\nI'm now integrating the UI for saved blueprint previews in the Local History Drawer, focusing on displaying key information for user clarity. I've successfully implemented the layout, incorporating the saved blueprint previews. I am finalizing the preview display now.\n\n\n**Refining History Interaction**\n\nI'm now implementing the interaction logic within the Local History Drawer. I'm focusing on user interactions, including how users select and view saved blueprints. I am ensuring that the retrieval of past blueprints is seamless.\n\n\n**Refining Delete Interaction**\n\nI'm now implementing the delete function within the history drawer, ensuring items are removed correctly. The implementation is based on the provided delete button in each record. The button's style has been reviewed. I'm focusing on user confirmation and feedback.\n\n\n"}}
